items.description:
Self-supported ride TWOHUNDOFUNDO Instagram

Saturday Jul 19, 2025 4:00 AM

Start: Brackett Park End: South Minneapolis

Distance: Up to 200 miles in a loop around the cities. Choose your own adventure, self-supported ride. Bring tools, flat fixing kit, food, water, and whatever else you need to be out biking all day.

Description: “A mixed terrain, ultra-endurance ride that is accessible to the masses. The perfect training ride, with numerous pull off points to make the ride as long or as short as you need.

Start at the beginning and go as long as you can, you will be surprised how far you go! Or meet up with some friends mid-route, and help them keep the party going! A true choose-your-own-adventure, unsanctioned and unsupported, the day is what you make it! Lot of places to rest, and even more places to turn off and shorten the ride, the stakes have never been lower!”

Group ride (no-drop) Bonesaw Cycling Collective group ride. Instagram.

Last Tuesday of every month. Meet at 6:45 pm, roll at 7 pm.

Start: Martin Olav Sabo Bridge. Finish: Sabo Bridge

Distance: typically 10-15 miles. Pace: typically 10 mph. 

This is a no-drop ride with a good mix between party pace and whistling pace and we will stay together with a dedicated leader and sweep.

Please bring all necessary supplies recommended for riding - layers, helmet, lock, emergency tools, tubes, snacks, etc. in case of emergency.
items.location: Martin Olav Sabo Bridge, Minneapolis, MN 55407, USA

Group ride (no-drop) EZ Bike Club Monthly Ride. Instagram.

6:30 pm social meet, 7:15pm roll out.

First Tuesday of every month through October.

Start: 1301 Theodore Wirth Parkway

Distance: Typically 10-15 miles. Pace: Chill pace, nobody left behind (likely 10-12 mph). 

Open to all. Bring lights. This ride is all about unity and movement, celebrating people of color on bikes, community connection, and the power of the outdoors in connection to our physical and mental well-being.

items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Midwest Dirt Legion, FTW Monarch brunch XC ride Ride Details. 

Date: Sunday Jul 13, 2025 10:00 AM - 12 PM.

Location: Monarch Singletrack Trailhead (6920 Springview Road Waconia, MN)

Who’s this for: “MDL hosts events specifically for marginalized genders. FTW / anyone but cis-men are welcome at our rides! Here’s a great resource defining FTW from our friends at GreaseRag.”

OPEN GROUP RIDE: We will be riding the XC trails so meet at the south trail head.  All skill levels welcome and we will break into groups as necessary so we all have a fun ride! This is a no drop ride so plan for plenty of time to stop and chat, scope out features, and generally bring the stoke!

items.summary: MDL - FTW Battle Creek Enduro Ride
items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Midwest Dirt Legion, FTW Battle Creek Enduro Ride Ride Details. 

Date: Thursday Jul 24, 2025 6:00 PM - 8 PM.

Location: 44.935151, -93.028772 Battle Creek lower parking lot

Who’s this for: “MDL hosts events specifically for marginalized genders. FTW / anyone but cis-men are welcome at our rides! Here’s a great resource defining FTW from our friends at GreaseRag.”


We'll be checking out the trails at Battle Creek, meet at the lower parking lot (Check the address) to learn names and get started! ENDURO RIDE: Battle Creek is known for it's awesome gravity trails which require a comfort on black trails with steep grades.  We will be climbing together and then staggering as we drop into these gravity trails before we regroup at the bottom.  Come get shreddy with us!

items.summary: MDL - FTW Dirt Church Cuyuna weekend
items.description:
Organized ride Midwest Dirt Legion Dirt Church Event details. Tickets. 

Date: Friday Aug 1, 2025 - Sunday Aug 3

Location: Cuyuna Country State Recreation Area

Who’s this for: “MDL hosts events specifically for marginalized genders. FTW / anyone but cis-men are welcome at our rides! Here’s a great resource defining FTW from our friends at GreaseRag.”

Cost: $50 (includes 2 nights camping + breakfast and more)

It’s time—our 4th annual Dirt Church is back and bigger than ever! (See website for full details)
 This year, we’re heading to an all-new location: the stunning red dirt trails of Cuyuna Country State Recreation Area! Pack your gear, grab your riding crew, and join us for a weekend of camping, community, and seriously fun singletrack.
What is Dirt Church?
 Hosted by MWDL, this weekend is all about creating joyful, welcoming riding spaces for marginalized genders—meaning this event is for anyone but cis-men. Whether you’re rolling solo or bringing the whole crew, you’ll find new friends, epic trails, and the kind of campfire vibes that keep you warm all year.

✨ Reduced-price tickets available for BIPOC riders.
items.location: Cuyuna Country State Recreation Area, 307 3rd St, Ironton, MN 56455, USA

items.summary: Wirth On Wednesdays (FTW week) MTB race
items.description:
Race (MTB) Wirth On Wednesdays MTB race Registration.
When: Every other Wednesday through August. Reg from 4:15pm to race start. Races at 5:30pm (2 lap and 1 lap races) and 6:20pm (4 lap and 3 lap races). Kids’ race at 6:00pm.
Location: The Trailhead (Theodore Wirth Park)

Who's this for:  Women & Non-Binary Week hosted by Unruly Women

  • Races this week are for those who identify as: Women, Non-Binary, Trans Women & Gender Expansive

  • *The kids races will remain open to all children*

  • ALL are welcome to celebrate, support and volunteer! 

See website for complete details. 3 mile laps on Theo wirth Area 36 MTB trails. Format for the series is mass start. We will have spacing in the start area and may have multiple waves depending on number of participants. Fat bikes are welcome, though there is no separate category for fat bikes. No e-bikes.
items.location: The Trailhead, 1221 Theodore Wirth Pkwy, Minneapolis, MN 55422, USA
